{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1772048170,"nonce":"xqvLwNkLBz05kbpbdH+fJOpkx7s=","message":"[GitHub comment by i-m-mll on 2026-02-05T04:24:40Z]\n\n## Use Case: Bulk Probe Addition via Selectors\n\nOne compelling use case for the selector API: **bulk probe addition** in the loss function UI.\n\nInstead of manually adding probes one-by-one, users could:\n\n```python\n# Select all RNN hidden state outputs\nselection = select(graph).at_instances_of(GRUCell).at_output_port('hidden')\n\n# Add probes to all of them\nfor node_id, port in selection.items():\n    add_probe(graph, node_id, port, name=f'{node_id}_hidden')\n```\n\nThis would enable workflows like:\n- \"Add probe to all hidden state outputs\" \n- \"Add probe to all Linear layer outputs\"\n- \"Add probe to all outputs of components tagged 'encoder'\"\n\nThe selector API makes these operations expressible in a single statement rather than manual enumeration.\n\nRelated: LOSS_UI_SPEC.md describes the probe mechanism; this would enhance the \"Advanced\" workflows.\n\n---\n*Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e*","files":null}]}